{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":537,"text":"I want to tell you"},{"time":2159,"text":"how 20,000 remarkable young people"},{"time":6850,"text":"from over 100 countries"},{"time":8706,"text":"ended up in Cuba"},{"time":10518,"text":"and are transforming health in their communities."},{"time":14321,"text":"Ninety percent of them would never"},{"time":16401,"text":"have left home at all"},{"time":17973,"text":"if it weren't for a scholarship\nto study medicine in Cuba"},{"time":21317,"text":"and a commitment to go back"},{"time":23128,"text":"to places like the ones they'd come from —"},{"time":26756,"text":"remote farmlands, mountains, ghettos —"},{"time":30203,"text":"to become doctors for people like themselves,"},{"time":33689,"text":"to walk the walk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35781,"text":"Havana's Latin American Medical School:"},{"time":38447,"text":"It's the largest medical school in the world,"},{"time":41372,"text":"graduating 23,000 young doctors"},{"time":44274,"text":"since its first class of 2005,"},{"time":47002,"text":"with nearly 10,000 more in the pipeline."},{"time":50611,"text":"Its mission, to train physicians for the people"},{"time":54432,"text":"who need them the most:"},{"time":56483,"text":"the over one billion"},{"time":58419,"text":"who have never seen a doctor,"},{"time":60682,"text":"the people who live and die"},{"time":64515,"text":"under every poverty line ever invented."},{"time":68009,"text":"Its students defy all norms."},{"time":70259,"text":"They're the school's biggest risk"},{"time":72530,"text":"and also its best bet."},{"time":74990,"text":"They're recruited from the poorest,"},{"time":77505,"text":"most broken places on our planet"},{"time":80076,"text":"by a school that believes they can become"},{"time":82350,"text":"not just the good"},{"time":83857,"text":"but the excellent physicians"},{"time":85792,"text":"their communities desperately need,"},{"time":88545,"text":"that they will practice where most doctors don't,"},{"time":92197,"text":"in places not only poor"},{"time":94623,"text":"but oftentimes dangerous,"},{"time":97176,"text":"carrying venom antidotes in their backpacks"},{"time":100202,"text":"or navigating neighborhoods"},{"time":102821,"text":"riddled by drugs, gangs and bullets,"},{"time":106142,"text":"their home ground."},{"time":108842,"text":"The hope is that they will help"},{"time":110168,"text":"transform access to care,"},{"time":112768,"text":"the health picture in impoverished areas,"},{"time":115187,"text":"and even the way medicine itself"},{"time":117346,"text":"is learned and practiced,"},{"time":119889,"text":"and that they will become pioneers in our global reach"},{"time":124140,"text":"for universal health coverage,"},{"time":126660,"text":"surely a tall order."},{"time":129378,"text":"Two big storms and this notion of \"walk the walk\""},{"time":133504,"text":"prompted creation of ELAM back in 1998."},{"time":137588,"text":"The Hurricanes Georges and Mitch"},{"time":140591,"text":"had ripped through the Caribbean"},{"time":142143,"text":"and Central America,"},{"time":144348,"text":"leaving 30,000 dead"},{"time":146727,"text":"and two and a half million homeless."},{"time":149610,"text":"Hundreds of Cuban doctors\nvolunteered for disaster response,"},{"time":153303,"text":"but when they got there,"},{"time":155148,"text":"they found a bigger disaster:"},{"time":157231,"text":"whole communities with no healthcare,"},{"time":160427,"text":"doors bolted shut on rural hospitals"},{"time":162751,"text":"for lack of staff,"},{"time":164630,"text":"and just too many babies dying"},{"time":167301,"text":"before their first birthday."},{"time":170236,"text":"What would happen when these Cuban doctors left?"},{"time":174070,"text":"New doctors were needed to make care sustainable,"},{"time":176784,"text":"but where would they come from?"},{"time":178096,"text":"Where would they train?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":180901,"text":"In Havana, the campus of a former naval academy"},{"time":185344,"text":"was turned over to the Cuban Health Ministry"},{"time":188269,"text":"to become the Latin American Medical School,"},{"time":191620,"text":"ELAM."},{"time":193633,"text":"Tuition, room and board, and a small stipend"},{"time":196107,"text":"were offered to hundreds of students"},{"time":198018,"text":"from the countries hardest hit by the storms."},{"time":201051,"text":"As a journalist in Havana,"},{"time":203330,"text":"I watched the first 97 Nicaraguans arrive"},{"time":206047,"text":"in March 1999,"},{"time":208589,"text":"settling into dorms barely refurbished"},{"time":211305,"text":"and helping their professors not\nonly sweep out the classrooms"},{"time":214984,"text":"but move in the desks and the\nchairs and the microscopes."},{"time":219663,"text":"Over the next few years,"},{"time":221542,"text":"governments throughout the Americas"},{"time":223454,"text":"requested scholarships for their own students,"},{"time":226627,"text":"and the Congressional Black Caucus"},{"time":228505,"text":"asked for and received hundreds of scholarships"},{"time":231880,"text":"for young people from the USA."},{"time":235120,"text":"Today, among the 23,000"},{"time":238832,"text":"are graduates from 83 countries"},{"time":241847,"text":"in the Americas, Africa and Asia,"},{"time":244851,"text":"and enrollment has grown to 123 nations."},{"time":250454,"text":"More than half the students are young women."},{"time":252658,"text":"They come from 100 ethnic groups,"},{"time":254050,"text":"speak 50 different languages."},{"time":256075,"text":"WHO Director Margaret Chan said,"},{"time":259216,"text":"\"For once, if you are poor, female,"},{"time":263254,"text":"or from an indigenous population,"},{"time":265516,"text":"you have a distinct advantage,"},{"time":267221,"text":"an ethic that makes this medical school unique.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":271950,"text":"Luther Castillo comes from San Pedro de Tocamacho"},{"time":276100,"text":"on the Atlantic coast of Honduras."},{"time":278970,"text":"There's no running water,"},{"time":280882,"text":"no electricity there,"},{"time":282682,"text":"and to reach the village, you have to walk for hours"},{"time":286282,"text":"or take your chances in a pickup truck like I did"},{"time":289195,"text":"skirting the waves of the Atlantic."},{"time":292490,"text":"Luther was one of 40 Tocamacho children"},{"time":297131,"text":"who started grammar school,"},{"time":299134,"text":"the sons and daughters of a black indigenous people"},{"time":301878,"text":"known as the Garífuna,"},{"time":303734,"text":"20 percent of the Honduran population."},{"time":307210,"text":"The nearest healthcare was fatal miles away."},{"time":312363,"text":"Luther had to walk three hours every day"},{"time":315850,"text":"to middle school."},{"time":317751,"text":"Only 17 made that trip."},{"time":319832,"text":"Only five went on to high school,"},{"time":321936,"text":"and only one to university:"},{"time":324100,"text":"Luther, to ELAM,"},{"time":326121,"text":"among the first crop of Garífuna graduates."},{"time":330130,"text":"Just two Garífuna doctors had preceded them"},{"time":333000,"text":"in all of Honduran history."},{"time":336044,"text":"Now there are 69, thanks to ELAM."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341945,"text":"Big problems need big solutions,"},{"time":345145,"text":"sparked by big ideas, imagination and audacity,"},{"time":348937,"text":"but also solutions that work."},{"time":351940,"text":"ELAM's faculty had no handy evidence base"},{"time":355270,"text":"to guide them, so they learned the hard way,"},{"time":358790,"text":"by doing and correcting course as they went."},{"time":362479,"text":"Even the brightest students"},{"time":364741,"text":"from these poor communities"},{"time":366654,"text":"weren't academically prepared"},{"time":368330,"text":"for six years of medical training,"},{"time":371023,"text":"so a bridging course was set up in sciences."},{"time":374680,"text":"Then came language:"},{"time":376255,"text":"these were Mapuche, Quechuas, Guaraní, Garífuna,"},{"time":379416,"text":"indigenous peoples"},{"time":381193,"text":"who learned Spanish as a second language,"},{"time":383393,"text":"or Haitians who spoke Creole."},{"time":386190,"text":"So Spanish became part"},{"time":388127,"text":"of the pre-pre-med curriculum."},{"time":392285,"text":"Even so, in Cuba,"},{"time":395227,"text":"the music, the food, the smells,"},{"time":398461,"text":"just about everything was different,"},{"time":401150,"text":"so faculty became family, ELAM home."},{"time":406155,"text":"Religions ranged from indigenous beliefs"},{"time":408968,"text":"to Yoruba, Muslim and Christian evangelical."},{"time":413000,"text":"Embracing diversity became a way of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417484,"text":"Why have so many countries"},{"time":419474,"text":"asked for these scholarships?"},{"time":421949,"text":"First, they just don't have enough doctors,"},{"time":425201,"text":"and where they do, their distribution"},{"time":426967,"text":"is skewed against the poor,"},{"time":429409,"text":"because our global health crisis"},{"time":431871,"text":"is fed by a crisis in human resources."},{"time":434836,"text":"We are short four to seven million health workers"},{"time":438688,"text":"just to meet basic needs,"},{"time":441152,"text":"and the problem is everywhere."},{"time":443010,"text":"Doctors are concentrated in the cities,"},{"time":445562,"text":"where only half the world's people live,"},{"time":448172,"text":"and within cities,"},{"time":449960,"text":"not in the shantytowns or South L.A."},{"time":454139,"text":"Here in the United States,"},{"time":455905,"text":"where we have healthcare reform,"},{"time":458406,"text":"we don't have the professionals we need."},{"time":460954,"text":"By 2020, we will be short"},{"time":463469,"text":"45,000 primary care physicians."},{"time":467608,"text":"And we're also part of the problem."},{"time":469765,"text":"The United States is the number one importer"},{"time":472232,"text":"of doctors from developing countries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476596,"text":"The second reasons students flock to Cuba"},{"time":479465,"text":"is the island's own health report card,"},{"time":481692,"text":"relying on strong primary care."},{"time":484662,"text":"A commission from The Lancet"},{"time":486484,"text":"rates Cuba among the best performing"},{"time":488990,"text":"middle-income countries in health."},{"time":491839,"text":"Save the Children ranks Cuba"},{"time":493785,"text":"the best country in Latin\nAmerica to become a mother."},{"time":498421,"text":"Cuba has similar life expectancy"},{"time":501410,"text":"and lower infant mortality than the United States,"},{"time":504642,"text":"with fewer disparities,"},{"time":506823,"text":"while spending per person"},{"time":508623,"text":"one 20th of what we do on health"},{"time":511638,"text":"here in the USA."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513787,"text":"Academically, ELAM is tough,"},{"time":516779,"text":"but 80 percent of its students graduate."},{"time":520410,"text":"The subjects are familiar —"},{"time":521756,"text":"basic and clinical sciences —"},{"time":524230,"text":"but there are major differences."},{"time":526656,"text":"First, training has moved out of the ivory tower"},{"time":530267,"text":"and into clinic classrooms and neighborhoods,"},{"time":533169,"text":"the kinds of places most of these grads will practice."},{"time":536533,"text":"Sure, they have lectures and hospital rotations too,"},{"time":540627,"text":"but community-based learning starts on day one."},{"time":545657,"text":"Second, students treat the whole patient,"},{"time":549423,"text":"mind and body,"},{"time":551337,"text":"in the context of their \nfamilies, their communities"},{"time":553843,"text":"and their culture."},{"time":555990,"text":"Third, they learn public health:"},{"time":558890,"text":"to assess their patients' drinking water, housing,"},{"time":561990,"text":"social and economic conditions."},{"time":565286,"text":"Fourth, they are taught"},{"time":567817,"text":"that a good patient interview"},{"time":570584,"text":"and a thorough clinical exam"},{"time":572688,"text":"provide most of the clues for diagnosis,"},{"time":575523,"text":"saving costly technology for confirmation."},{"time":579426,"text":"And finally, they're taught over and over again"},{"time":582976,"text":"the importance of prevention,"},{"time":585020,"text":"especially as chronic diseases"},{"time":587420,"text":"cripple health systems worldwide."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591580,"text":"Such an in-service learning"},{"time":594770,"text":"also comes with a team approach,"},{"time":597370,"text":"as much how to work in teams"},{"time":600237,"text":"as how to lead them,"},{"time":602183,"text":"with a dose of humility."},{"time":604310,"text":"Upon graduation, these doctors share"},{"time":607110,"text":"their knowledge with nurse's aids, midwives,"},{"time":609820,"text":"community health workers,"},{"time":611790,"text":"to help them become better at what they do,"},{"time":614176,"text":"not to replace them,"},{"time":616121,"text":"to work with shamans and traditional healers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":621311,"text":"ELAM's graduates:"},{"time":623870,"text":"Are they proving this audacious experiment right?"},{"time":628527,"text":"Dozens of projects give us an inkling"},{"time":630822,"text":"of what they're capable of doing."},{"time":633390,"text":"Take the Garífuna grads."},{"time":635153,"text":"They not only went to work back home,"},{"time":637343,"text":"but they organized their communities to build"},{"time":639750,"text":"Honduras' first indigenous hospital."},{"time":643151,"text":"With an architect's help,"},{"time":645300,"text":"residents literally raised it from the ground up."},{"time":649777,"text":"The first patients walked through the doors"},{"time":651959,"text":"in December 2007,"},{"time":654299,"text":"and since then, the hospital has received"},{"time":656808,"text":"nearly one million patient visits."},{"time":659958,"text":"And government is paying attention,"},{"time":662119,"text":"upholding the hospital as a model"},{"time":664640,"text":"of rural public health for Honduras."}]},{"cues":[{"time":669819,"text":"ELAM's graduates are smart,"},{"time":673467,"text":"strong and also dedicated."},{"time":676920,"text":"Haiti, January 2010."},{"time":681274,"text":"The pain."},{"time":683109,"text":"People buried under 30 million tons of rubble."},{"time":687112,"text":"Overwhelming."},{"time":689261,"text":"Three hundred forty Cuban doctors"},{"time":691139,"text":"were already on the ground long term."},{"time":693580,"text":"More were on their way. Many more were needed."},{"time":695983,"text":"At ELAM, students worked round the clock"},{"time":699227,"text":"to contact 2,000 graduates."},{"time":702445,"text":"As a result, hundreds arrived in Haiti,"},{"time":705629,"text":"27 countries' worth, from Mali in the Sahara"},{"time":709926,"text":"to St. Lucia, Bolivia, Chile and the USA."},{"time":714414,"text":"They spoke easily to each other in Spanish"},{"time":717710,"text":"and listened to their patients in Creole"},{"time":720399,"text":"thanks to Haitian medical students"},{"time":722525,"text":"flown in from ELAM in Cuba."},{"time":724752,"text":"Many stayed for months,"},{"time":726440,"text":"even through the cholera epidemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729218,"text":"Hundreds of Haitian graduates"},{"time":731558,"text":"had to pick up the pieces,"},{"time":734280,"text":"overcome their own heartbreak,"},{"time":736294,"text":"and then pick up the burden"},{"time":738160,"text":"of building a new public health system for Haiti."},{"time":741728,"text":"Today, with aid of organizations and governments"},{"time":744225,"text":"from Norway to Cuba to Brazil,"},{"time":746778,"text":"dozens of new health centers have been built,"},{"time":749004,"text":"staffed, and in 35 cases, headed"},{"time":752575,"text":"by ELAM graduates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756497,"text":"Yet the Haitian story"},{"time":758365,"text":"also illustrates some of the bigger problems"},{"time":760424,"text":"faced in many countries."},{"time":762640,"text":"Take a look:"},{"time":764384,"text":"748 Haitian graduates by \n2012, when cholera struck,"},{"time":770166,"text":"nearly half working in the public health sector"},{"time":773912,"text":"but one quarter unemployed,"},{"time":775983,"text":"and 110 had left Haiti altogether."},{"time":782093,"text":"So in the best case scenarios,"},{"time":784861,"text":"these graduates are staffing"},{"time":786731,"text":"and thus strengthening public health systems,"},{"time":789980,"text":"where often they're the only doctors around."},{"time":793159,"text":"In the worst cases, there are simply not enough jobs"},{"time":795950,"text":"in the public health sector,"},{"time":797592,"text":"where most poor people are treated,"},{"time":800158,"text":"not enough political will, not enough resources,"},{"time":802957,"text":"not enough anything —"},{"time":805163,"text":"just too many patients with no care."},{"time":808616,"text":"The grads face pressure from their families too,"},{"time":811600,"text":"desperate to make ends meet,"},{"time":813903,"text":"so when there are no public sector jobs,"},{"time":816479,"text":"these new MDs decamp into private practice,"},{"time":819100,"text":"or go abroad to send money home."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823115,"text":"Worst of all, in some countries,"},{"time":826300,"text":"medical societies influence accreditation bodies"},{"time":829236,"text":"not to honor the ELAM degree,"},{"time":832251,"text":"fearful these grads will take their jobs"},{"time":834568,"text":"or reduce their patient loads and income."},{"time":838123,"text":"It's not a question of competencies."},{"time":841104,"text":"Here in the USA, the California Medical Board"},{"time":843612,"text":"accredited the school after rigorous inspection,"},{"time":847212,"text":"and the new physicians are making good"},{"time":849260,"text":"on Cuba's big bet,"},{"time":851451,"text":"passing their boards and accepted"},{"time":853262,"text":"into highly respected residencies"},{"time":855647,"text":"from New York to Chicago to New Mexico."},{"time":859738,"text":"Two hundred strong, they're coming"},{"time":862363,"text":"back to the United States energized,"},{"time":864748,"text":"and also dissatisfied."},{"time":867335,"text":"As one grad put it,"},{"time":868966,"text":"in Cuba, \"We are trained to provide quality care"},{"time":872420,"text":"with minimal resources,"},{"time":874422,"text":"so when I see all the resources we have here,"},{"time":876998,"text":"and you tell me that's not possible,"},{"time":879160,"text":"I know it's not true."},{"time":881330,"text":"Not only have I seen it work, I've done the work.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":886949,"text":"ELAM's graduates,"},{"time":888910,"text":"some from right here in D.C. and Baltimore,"},{"time":892427,"text":"have come from the poorest of the poor"},{"time":895595,"text":"to offer health, education"},{"time":897928,"text":"and a voice to their communities."},{"time":900844,"text":"They've done the heavy lifting."},{"time":903496,"text":"Now we need to do our part"},{"time":905510,"text":"to support the 23,000 and counting,"},{"time":909127,"text":"All of us —"},{"time":910481,"text":"foundations, residency directors, press,"},{"time":914115,"text":"entrepreneurs, policymakers, people —"},{"time":917299,"text":"need to step up."},{"time":919452,"text":"We need to do much more globally"},{"time":921443,"text":"to give these new doctors the opportunity"},{"time":924382,"text":"to prove their mettle."},{"time":926775,"text":"They need to be able"},{"time":927778,"text":"to take their countries' licensing exams."},{"time":930982,"text":"They need jobs in the public health sector"},{"time":933930,"text":"or in nonprofit health centers"},{"time":935685,"text":"to put their training and commitment to work."},{"time":939532,"text":"They need the chance to be"},{"time":941815,"text":"the doctors their patients need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946674,"text":"To move forward,"},{"time":948531,"text":"we may have to find our way back"},{"time":951523,"text":"to that pediatrician who would"},{"time":953706,"text":"knock on my family's door"},{"time":955393,"text":"on the South Side of Chicago when I was a kid,"},{"time":958579,"text":"who made house calls,"},{"time":960489,"text":"who was a public servant."},{"time":963380,"text":"These aren't such new ideas"},{"time":965203,"text":"of what medicine should be."},{"time":967565,"text":"What's new is the scaling up"},{"time":970290,"text":"and the faces of the doctors themselves:"},{"time":973673,"text":"an ELAM graduate is more likely to be a she"},{"time":977130,"text":"than a he;"},{"time":979060,"text":"In the Amazon, Peru or Guatemala,"},{"time":981987,"text":"an indigenous doctor;"},{"time":984338,"text":"in the USA, a doctor of color"},{"time":987352,"text":"who speaks fluent Spanish."},{"time":989748,"text":"She is well trained, can be counted on,"},{"time":993427,"text":"and shares the face and culture of her patients,"},{"time":997071,"text":"and she deserves our support surely,"},{"time":1000480,"text":"because whether by subway, mule, or canoe,"},{"time":1004946,"text":"she is teaching us to walk the walk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1007944,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}